<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880302-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: United Technologies Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UTX MS </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   United Technologies Corp., Hartford, Conn., completed the sale of the domestic operations of Essex Group Inc. in a leveraged buy-out led by Morgan Stanley Group Inc., the New York securities firm.    United Technologies, which among other things makes plane engines, also has announced an agreement to sell the European operations of Essex to Von Roll AG, of Gerlafingen, Switzerland. The combined proceeds for both sales will exceed $475 million, the company said.    Essex Group, based in Fort Wayne, Ind., makes wire and cable. Its 1987 domestic sales were $737 million.    A leveraged buy-out is the purchase of a company by a group of investors, financed largely through debt. Ultimately the debt is paid with funds generated by the acquired company's operations or the sale of its assets. </TEXT></DOC>